<bibRefCitation author="Smith, J. L. B." box="[994,1139,1607,1632]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="373 - 418" refId="ref35841" refString="Smith, J. L. B. (1961) Fishes of the family Apogonidae of the western Indian Ocean and the Red Sea. Ichthyology Bulletin, 22, 373 - 418." type="journal article" year="1961">Smith, 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, T. H." box="[1154,1294,1607,1632]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref32750" refString="Fraser, T. H. (1972) Comparative osteology of the shallow water cardinal fishes (Perciformes: Apogonidae) with references to the systematics and evolution of the family. Ichthyological Bulletin of the J. L. B. Smith Institute of Ichthyology, 34, i - v + 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1972">
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1224,1608,1631]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="176" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Fraser">Fraser</taxonomicName>
1972
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baldwin, C. C. &amp; Johnson, G. D." pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="1050 - 1073" refId="ref31432" refString="Baldwin, C. C. &amp; Johnson, G. D. (1999) Paxton concilians: a new genus and species of Pseudamine apogonid (Teleostei: Percoidei) from northwestern Australia: the sister group of the enigmatic Gymnapogon. Copeia, 1999 (4), 1050 - 1073. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1447980" type="journal article" year="1999">Baldwin &amp; Johnson 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergman, L. M. R." box="[327,497,1644,1669]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" refId="ref31499" refString="Bergman, L. M. R. (2004) The cephalic lateralis system of cardinalfishes (Perciformes: Apogonidae) and its application to the taxonomy and systematics of the family. Dissertation, University of Hawaii, Honolulu, Hawaii, 373 pp." type="book" year="2004">Bergman 2004</bibRefCitation>
) as belonging in this subfamily. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Thacker, C. E. &amp; Roje, D. M." box="[999,1288,1644,1669]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="735 - 745" refId="ref36243" refString="Thacker, C. E. &amp; Roje, D. M. (2009) Phylogeny of cardinalfishes (Teleostei: Gobiiformes: Apogonidae) and the evolution of visceral bioluminescence. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 52, 735 - 745. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2009.05.017" type="journal article" year="2009">Thacker &amp; Roje's (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cowman, P. F. &amp; Bellwood, D. R." pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="2543 - 2562" refId="ref32256" refString="Cowman, P. F. &amp; Bellwood, D. R. (2011) Coral reefs as drivers of cladogenesis: expanding coral reefs, cryptic extinction events, and the development of biodiversity hotspots. Journal of Evolutionary Biology, 24, 2543 - 2562. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1420 - 9101.2011.02391. x" type="journal article" year="2011">Cowman &amp; Bellwood's (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, and the present molecular analyses placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[856,981,1679,1704]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[856,981,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Pseudamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
outside the rest of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1859" box="[1241,1378,1679,1704]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Apogonidae</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,302,1716,1739]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Gymnapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,302,1716,1739]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Gymnapogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nested into the latter large clade (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1954" box="[705,854,1716,1741]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[705,854,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Pseudamiops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was absent from these studies). Corresponding to such phylogenetic relationship, monophyly between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[740,864,1751,1776]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[740,864,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Pseudamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1905" box="[919,1070,1752,1775]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Gymnapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[919,1070,1752,1775]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Gymnapogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(H14) was significantly rejected by the AU test based on the present molecular data (
<tableCitation box="[749,837,1788,1813]" captionStart="TABLE 6" captionStartId="14.[147,235,642,665]" captionTargetId="graphics-45@14.[131,1870,682,1530]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="TABLE 6. Statistical likelihood-based AU tests between unconstrained and constrained trees." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/16E9AFE381160B1DFF7CC4EAFBDFD4E2" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" tableUuid="16E9AFE381160B1DFF7CC4EAFBDFD4E2">Table 6</tableCitation>
). All 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[903,1028,1788,1813]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,1028,1788,1813]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Pseudamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have two scaled lateral lines on the body, hypurals 1 and 2 fused, urostylar sheath over hypurals 3 and 4, one reduced pair of uroneurals in anterior position, all possible synapomorphies. The comparative morphological features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[1076,1200,1860,1885]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1200,1860,1885]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Pseudamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reductive, fusion and loss of bones (
<bibRefCitation author="Baldwin, C. C. &amp; Johnson, G. D." box="[384,701,1895,1920]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="1050 - 1073" refId="ref31432" refString="Baldwin, C. C. &amp; Johnson, G. D. (1999) Paxton concilians: a new genus and species of Pseudamine apogonid (Teleostei: Percoidei) from northwestern Australia: the sister group of the enigmatic Gymnapogon. Copeia, 1999 (4), 1050 - 1073. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1447980" type="journal article" year="1999">Baldwin &amp; Johnson, 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Many of these reductive features are held in common with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,302,1932,1955]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Gymnapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,302,1932,1955]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Gymnapogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Randall &amp; Smith 1988" authorityName="Randall &amp; Smith" authorityYear="1988" box="[319,704,1932,1957]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Cercamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[319,428,1932,1955]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Cercamia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Randall J. E. &amp; Smith, C. L." box="[438,704,1932,1957]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref35345" refString="Randall J. E. &amp; Smith, C. L. (1988) Two new species and a new genus of cardinalfishes (Perciformes: Apogonidae) from Rapa, South Pacific Ocean. American Museum Novitates, 2926, 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1988">Randall &amp; Smith 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser &amp; Struhsaker 1991" authorityName="Fraser &amp; Struhsaker" authorityYear="1991" box="[718,1165,1932,1957]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Lachneratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[718,858,1932,1957]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Lachneratus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, T. H. &amp; Struhsaker, P. J." box="[868,1165,1932,1957]" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" pagination="718 - 722" refId="ref33106" refString="Fraser, T. H. &amp; Struhsaker, P. J. (1991) A new genus and species of cardinalfish (Apogonidae) from the Indo-West Pacific, with a key to Apogonine genera. Copeia, 1991 (3), 718 - 722. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1446398" type="journal article" year="1991">Fraser &amp; Struhsaker 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1954" box="[1226,1375,1932,1957]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1226,1375,1932,1957]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Pseudamiops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter four genera are all translucent when alive unlike most (all?) species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[1103,1227,1968,1993]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1103,1227,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Pseudamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Body shapes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,302,2004,2027]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Gymnapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,302,2004,2027]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Gymnapogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Randall &amp; Smith" authorityYear="1988" box="[315,425,2004,2027]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Cercamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,425,2004,2027]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Cercamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser &amp; Struhsaker" authorityYear="1991" box="[478,618,2004,2029]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Lachneratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="177" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[478,618,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="177">Lachneratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include forked caudal fins and the latter two genera have large scales and lack pored lateral-line scales. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1954" box="[484,633,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Pseudamiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[484,633,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Pseudamiops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not part of this study and is removed from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1954" box="[1210,1366,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudamiinae">Pseudamiinae</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1941" box="[151,333,188,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Gymnapogonini">Gymnapogonini</taxonomicName>
based on its body being translucent, having large scales without pored lateral-line scales. The conflict between using molecular and morphological information independently supporting differing hypotheses remains confounding for these five genera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
Living pseudamine fishes have virtually no morphological characters that are considered basal for apogonids as restricted here. All are derived characters from those states present in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabuchi &amp; Fraser &amp; Song &amp; Azuma &amp; Nishida" authorityYear="2014" box="[1094,1226,332,357]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Amioidinae">Amioidinae</taxonomicName>
and in the basal 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1859" box="[151,292,367,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Apogoninae">Apogoninae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Baldwin, C. C. &amp; Johnson, G. D." box="[301,604,367,392]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="1050 - 1073" refId="ref31432" refString="Baldwin, C. C. &amp; Johnson, G. D. (1999) Paxton concilians: a new genus and species of Pseudamine apogonid (Teleostei: Percoidei) from northwestern Australia: the sister group of the enigmatic Gymnapogon. Copeia, 1999 (4), 1050 - 1073. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1447980" type="journal article" year="1999">Baldwin &amp; Johnson (1999)</bibRefCitation>
listed plesiomorphic characters for the expanded pseudamine fishes. They did not include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraser &amp; Struhsaker" authorityYear="1991" box="[326,466,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Lachneratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[326,466,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Lachneratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Randall &amp; Smith" authorityYear="1988" box="[503,612,404,427]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Apogonidae" genus="Cercamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[503,612,404,427]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Cercamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as part of the pseudamine group.
</paragraph>
